{"kind":"blogger#post","id":"7183114549778848189","blog":{"id":"2360593805083673688"},"published":"2011-06-15T07:00:00-07:00","updated":"2011-06-15T07:00:03-07:00","url":"http://www.quietlikehorses.com/2011/06/fresh-finds-from-santa-clara-farmers.html","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/7183114549778848189","title":"Fresh Finds from the Santa Clara Farmers' Market","content":"<a href=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-6LMqCH5OKAA/TfhRT-gVXSI/AAAAAAAAGzM/tkxPLzleJrQ/s1600/peaches%2Band%2Bplums.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img style=\"display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 600px; height: 400px;\" src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-6LMqCH5OKAA/TfhRT-gVXSI/AAAAAAAAGzM/tkxPLzleJrQ/s1600/peaches%2Band%2Bplums.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5618329938782674210\" /></a><div style=\"text-align: center;\">{peaches, plums, and nectarines}</div><div><br /><div>I've been a fan of farmers' markets for a few years now, but just in the past few weeks have I really started to appreciate the one in my own neighborhood. Yes, the one in Santa Clara is just a couple blocks long, but it still has all the essentials of what I consider a good farmers' market: fresh fruit, flowers, and food stands for picking up a quick breakfast while you stroll. This weekend I bought peaches to make <a href=\"http://bit.ly/iwA6Ou\">this peach pie</a> and flowers from the sweetest lady. She sells her flowers at the best prices I've ever seen -- the hydrangeas below cost $3 (they look a bit wilted from being in my trunk for 6 hours but later revived themselves just fine). I can't wait to visit throughout the season to see how the produce selection changes and to stock up on $3 bouquets!  <div><br /><a href=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-jTbTB_lwVkc/TfhRTTa36rI/AAAAAAAAGzE/3ehJiBex-bA/s1600/flowers.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img style=\"display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 600px; height: 895px;\" src=\"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-jTbTB_lwVkc/TfhRTTa36rI/AAAAAAAAGzE/3ehJiBex-bA/s1600/flowers.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5618329927217048242\" /></a><div style=\"text-align: center;\">{Flowers really do brighten up a room. I think I'm becoming addicted to having them around.}</div><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><br /></div><a href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-XauVj7sNzvw/TfhRTNz7j4I/AAAAAAAAGy8/Tmfejm3K3pE/s1600/cherry.jpg\" onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\"><img style=\"display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 600px; height: 400px;\" src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-XauVj7sNzvw/TfhRTNz7j4I/AAAAAAAAGy8/Tmfejm3K3pE/s1600/cherry.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5618329925711531906\" /></a><div style=\"text-align: center;\">{perfect snack to eat on the walk back home}</div></div></div></div>","author":{"id":"06629562195146939698","displayName":"Sobrina Tung","url":"http://www.blogger.com/profile/06629562195146939698","image":{"url":"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TI8X4CO5nWI/AAAAAAAAERk/4p5D74gYdFE/S45/me.JPG"}},"replies":{"totalItems":"2","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/7183114549778848189/comments"},"labels":["To See"]}